WEBVTT

00:06.863 --> 00:10.186
- [exhales]

00:10.266 --> 00:12.068
Well, that was weird.

00:12.148 --> 00:13.470
- Really weird.
- Mm-hmm.

00:13.550 --> 00:15.271
- Maybe we never
try that again.

00:15.352 --> 00:16.993
- Mm-hmm.

00:17.073 --> 00:19.115
You're the one who
suggested that we...

00:19.195 --> 00:21.037
switch...

00:21.117 --> 00:22.719
to opposite sides of the bed

00:22.799 --> 00:25.121
to see if we liked
the other better,

00:25.201 --> 00:26.963
and I kept waking up confused.

00:27.043 --> 00:28.044
I didn't know where I was.

00:28.124 --> 00:30.447
- Well, I'm sorry, buddy.

00:30.527 --> 00:32.008
You're here

00:32.088 --> 00:33.850
in my bedroom,

00:33.930 --> 00:36.172
stuck with me.

00:36.252 --> 00:38.975
- Lucky me.

00:40.136 --> 00:43.219
- I've really enjoyed
these past few weeks together.

00:43.299 --> 00:45.422
They've made me feel
much closer to you.

00:45.502 --> 00:46.383
- Oh, yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

00:46.463 --> 00:48.064
- Hmm.

00:48.144 --> 00:49.786
And there's still so much more
you have to learn.

00:49.866 --> 00:51.267
I mean, there must be
a million things

00:51.347 --> 00:53.790
we don't know about each other.

00:53.870 --> 00:54.951
- There are?

00:55.031 --> 00:56.713
- Well, I bet you
didn't know that

00:56.793 --> 00:59.756
I am a part of an elite
weekly woodworking club.

00:59.836 --> 01:01.798
- Like sawing, and hammering,
and making wood stuff?

01:01.878 --> 01:03.239
- In an elite way.

01:03.319 --> 01:05.562
- Okay.
[laughter]

01:05.642 --> 01:08.725
- What about you,
what are some things about you

01:08.805 --> 01:10.927
that I would not
be able to guess?

01:11.007 --> 01:13.810
- Mm...

01:13.890 --> 01:15.892
Let me think.

01:21.177 --> 01:23.219
Oh, you know how short I am?

01:23.299 --> 01:24.260
Is that a secret?

01:24.340 --> 01:25.542
- No.

01:25.622 --> 01:27.944
Try again.
- No?

01:28.024 --> 01:30.467
Oh.

01:30.547 --> 01:33.069
Today, Mo is taking me to see
a professional medium.

01:33.149 --> 01:34.871
It was his
birthday present to me,

01:34.951 --> 01:36.873
and we're gonna
use it to contact my father.

01:36.953 --> 01:38.955
- I didn't know
you believed in that stuff.

01:39.035 --> 01:41.037
- I'm not sure I do,
but we'll see what happens.

01:41.117 --> 01:43.039
- Just be careful, okay?

01:43.119 --> 01:45.602
My mom was totally scammed
by a shady psychic

01:45.682 --> 01:48.485
after my dad died, and...

01:48.565 --> 01:50.847
they can be
real grief vampires, so.

01:50.927 --> 01:53.450
- [imitating Dracula] Well,
I'll have to bring some garlic

01:53.530 --> 01:55.452
to protect myself.

01:55.532 --> 01:57.734
Mwahahahahaha.

01:57.814 --> 02:01.177
Oh, another secret is I like
to do voices sometimes.

02:04.140 --> 02:05.622
Hey, Mom?

02:05.702 --> 02:07.984
Can I borrow Dad's fancy watch
for the day?

02:08.064 --> 02:10.026
The medium requires
a personal object

02:10.106 --> 02:12.308
to connect to the other side.
- Oh, yeah, sure.

02:12.388 --> 02:14.551
Just don't read the
inscription on the back.

02:14.631 --> 02:17.033
It's kind of
an inside and dirty joke

02:17.113 --> 02:18.475
Do you want
to grab a plate, sweetie?

02:18.555 --> 02:20.917
- No, Mo's actually
waiting for me

02:20.997 --> 02:22.278
and, you know,
maybe so is Dad.

02:22.358 --> 02:23.840
- Well, yeah.

02:23.920 --> 02:25.121
He's probably hanging out
with Elvis and Larry King.

02:25.201 --> 02:26.362
- This was a gift,

02:26.442 --> 02:28.605
so I don't know how
this is gonna go,

02:28.685 --> 02:30.527
but if anyone
has a question for Dad,

02:30.607 --> 02:31.928
let me know.

02:32.008 --> 02:34.010
- Ask him how he feels
about me quitting my job

02:34.090 --> 02:35.011
and if he still loves me.

02:35.091 --> 02:36.773
- You can tell him

02:36.853 --> 02:38.414
that I miss him
every single day,

02:38.495 --> 02:40.216
and, um,

02:40.296 --> 02:42.258
if you could find out what he
did with that rice cooker,

02:42.338 --> 02:44.140
I need it for
a dinner party thing.

02:44.220 --> 02:45.902
- You're having
a dinner party thingy?

02:45.982 --> 02:47.704
- The Millers and the
Blausteins are coming over.

02:47.784 --> 02:49.706
Nothing fancy,
but after your birthday,

02:49.786 --> 02:52.228
I decided maybe it's time
to be social again.

02:52.308 --> 02:54.390
Come on, let's go get you
that watch.

02:54.470 --> 02:55.752
- Hey Zoey,
maybe ask the psychic

02:55.832 --> 02:56.993
if I'll ever feel joy again?

02:57.073 --> 02:59.155
- Ha.

02:59.235 --> 03:01.237
I will, sure.

03:02.959 --> 03:04.961
This is the psychic?

03:05.041 --> 03:06.563
Is she gonna read my mind

03:06.643 --> 03:07.804
or is she gonna
knit me a sweater?

03:07.884 --> 03:10.246
- She's done both for me,
but she's not a psychic.

03:10.326 --> 03:12.529
She prefers the term
"intuitive."

03:12.609 --> 03:14.611
- Who wants fizzy water?

03:14.691 --> 03:16.332
I only have pamplemousse.

03:16.412 --> 03:19.816
- Sounds good, Nova.
I only drink pamplemousse.

03:22.418 --> 03:24.420
- Here you go.

03:26.903 --> 03:29.385
Dead people make me thirsty.

03:37.073 --> 03:39.676
- Oh, that's part
of her process.

03:41.758 --> 03:43.079
- Okay, so how do we do this?

03:43.159 --> 03:44.721
Do I just start talking?

03:44.801 --> 03:47.283
Like, "Hey, Dad,
are you up there listening?

03:47.363 --> 03:49.525
Knock twice
if you can hear me."

03:51.407 --> 03:53.369
- I wish people
would have an open mind

03:53.449 --> 03:55.291
about other people's
special abilities.

03:55.371 --> 03:56.653
- [mouthing words]

03:56.733 --> 03:58.615
- You know,
it is so easy to mock

03:58.695 --> 04:00.697
what you do not understand.

04:02.298 --> 04:03.740
Did you bring an item
of your father's?

04:03.820 --> 04:05.622
- Uh,

04:05.702 --> 04:07.704
I did.

04:13.189 --> 04:14.711
Oh, d--

04:14.791 --> 04:16.232
- [giggles]

04:16.312 --> 04:18.474
Spicy.

04:18.554 --> 04:20.997
Okay, let's begin.

04:28.845 --> 04:30.086
Sorry about that.

04:30.166 --> 04:31.808
Building has
electrical problems,

04:31.888 --> 04:33.850
Or...

04:33.930 --> 04:35.892
you and I have a deep

04:35.972 --> 04:38.414
psychological connection.

04:41.017 --> 04:43.219
One or the other.

04:43.299 --> 04:45.541
Now I'm sensing that

04:45.622 --> 04:49.105
there is something not right
inside of you.

04:49.185 --> 04:50.907
- That's 'cause
she ain't right.

04:50.987 --> 04:53.149
- You're really dark inside.

04:53.229 --> 04:54.791
Wait, not dark, no.

04:54.871 --> 04:56.833
Mixed-up.

04:56.913 --> 04:58.554
But your dad, uh...

04:58.635 --> 05:00.436
now he's trying to communicate.

05:00.516 --> 05:02.038
Is there any way,

05:02.118 --> 05:03.840
and I know this is probably
not gonna make much sense

05:03.920 --> 05:05.682
to you at first,

05:05.762 --> 05:07.644
but, uh,

05:07.724 --> 05:09.846
did your Dad

05:09.926 --> 05:12.328
like

05:12.408 --> 05:14.250
movies?

05:14.330 --> 05:16.252
- [scoffs]
Yeah.

05:16.332 --> 05:18.414
My dad,

05:18.494 --> 05:21.457
like most humans
on planet Earth,

05:21.537 --> 05:22.859
enjoyed movies.

05:22.939 --> 05:24.821
- Baby, not my Auntie June.

05:24.901 --> 05:26.382
She went to go see
"Marley &amp; Me",

05:26.462 --> 05:27.904
and she never went back.

05:27.984 --> 05:30.306
- Oh, oh, God.
He's fading.

05:30.386 --> 05:33.149
He's fading.

05:33.229 --> 05:35.591
[sighs] He's gone.

05:35.672 --> 05:37.914
- Okay, he's gone.
That's it.

05:37.994 --> 05:40.636
- Yeah, that's it.

05:47.123 --> 05:48.725
- Okay.

05:48.805 --> 05:50.246
How is any of this real?

05:50.326 --> 05:52.368
- How are your powers real?
- I don't know.

05:52.448 --> 05:54.290
But if Simon's gonna look at me
the way that I was just

05:54.370 --> 05:56.012
looking at Nova,
then I'm never telling him

05:56.092 --> 05:58.094
about my powers.

05:58.775 --> 06:01.818
- Shift is over and I am free.

06:01.898 --> 06:03.259
- Waiting for Rose?

06:03.339 --> 06:05.261
- Uh, yeah.
You waiting for Simon?

06:05.341 --> 06:07.263
- Yeah.
Look at us.

06:07.343 --> 06:08.504
Waiting for dates.

06:08.584 --> 06:09.906
- And being
totally chill about it.

06:09.986 --> 06:11.107
- How are you two doing?

06:11.187 --> 06:14.070
- Honestly,
things are going pretty--

06:15.671 --> 06:18.554
[soft piano music]

06:18.634 --> 06:25.521
♪ ♪

06:29.966 --> 06:33.329
♪ A hundred million stories
and a hundred million songs ♪

06:33.409 --> 06:36.212
♪ And I feel stupid
when I sing ♪

06:36.292 --> 06:39.575
♪ Nobody's listening to me ♪

06:39.655 --> 06:44.260
♪ Nobody's listening ♪

06:44.340 --> 06:47.824
♪ I talk to shooting stars,
but they always get it wrong ♪

06:47.904 --> 06:50.867
♪ I feel stupid when I pray ♪

06:50.947 --> 06:54.350
♪ So why am I praying anyway ♪

06:54.430 --> 06:59.115
♪ If nobody's listening ♪

06:59.195 --> 07:01.517
♪ Anyone ♪

07:01.597 --> 07:05.321
♪ Please send me anyone ♪

07:05.401 --> 07:09.165
♪ Lord, is there anyone? ♪

07:09.245 --> 07:12.528
♪ I need someone ♪

07:12.608 --> 07:16.372
♪ Oh, anyone ♪

07:16.452 --> 07:20.016
♪ Please send me anyone ♪

07:20.096 --> 07:24.140
♪ Lord, is there anyone? ♪

07:24.220 --> 07:28.224
♪ I need someone ♪

07:36.953 --> 07:38.875
Things are going pretty great.

07:38.955 --> 07:41.117
No complaints, so...

07:41.197 --> 07:42.839
What?

07:42.919 --> 07:44.640
What's wrong?

07:44.720 --> 07:48.124
- Uh, you just sang

07:48.204 --> 07:51.327
the most deeply sad

07:51.407 --> 07:53.930
and haunting heart song
I've ever heard

07:54.010 --> 07:55.411
in my life.

07:55.491 --> 07:57.053
- Really?

07:57.133 --> 07:58.935
I don't know why.

07:59.015 --> 08:01.697
I mean, I was just thinking
about how positive things are.

08:01.777 --> 08:03.739
Rose and I are going to
Happy Times Fun Land tonight.

08:03.820 --> 08:05.661
- Hey, hi you two.
- Hey.

08:05.741 --> 08:07.143
- Hey, oh, Zoey,

08:07.223 --> 08:08.744
I'm really glad
that you're here.

08:08.825 --> 08:10.426
My friend is having
an art show this week,

08:10.506 --> 08:12.188
and it's all
computer-themed pieces.

08:12.268 --> 08:14.070
I thought maybe you two
tech-heads would want to go.

08:14.150 --> 08:15.311
- Yeah, sure.
That sounds great.

08:15.391 --> 08:16.552
Thanks, Rose.

08:16.632 --> 08:17.874
- Cool, I'll get your email
from Max.

08:17.954 --> 08:19.475
- See?

08:19.555 --> 08:21.597
Sad people don't party at
Happy Times Fun Land.

08:21.677 --> 08:23.759
Not tonight they don't.

08:23.840 --> 08:25.361
- Hmm...

08:25.441 --> 08:28.524
Something about this is really

08:28.604 --> 08:30.887
fu...

08:30.967 --> 08:32.969
...nky.

08:34.730 --> 08:37.253
[rock music]

08:42.218 --> 08:44.060
- Hey, can I come in?

08:44.140 --> 08:45.501
I'm not interrupting anything,
am I?

08:45.581 --> 08:48.064
- No, but you will see
a "Do Not Disturb" sign

08:48.144 --> 08:49.625
on my door later this evening
that I stole

08:49.705 --> 08:51.107
from the Ritz Carlton.

08:51.187 --> 08:52.989
Perry and I are having
our first sleepover.

08:53.069 --> 08:54.750
- Ooh, are you gonna
build a fort?

08:54.830 --> 08:56.192
- Don't do that.

08:56.272 --> 08:58.474
But I am gonna go sit over
there right now

08:58.554 --> 09:00.596
and watch a marathon of
"Law &amp; Order: SVU."

09:00.676 --> 09:01.998
Do you need something?

09:02.078 --> 09:03.960
- I think my powers
are malfunctioning again.

09:04.040 --> 09:06.122
- Malfunctioning how?
You only hear jazz.

09:06.202 --> 09:07.523
Oh, you only hear animals.

09:07.603 --> 09:09.325
You only hear
animals singing jazz.

09:09.405 --> 09:12.208
- No, I heard Max sing this
heartbreaking,

09:12.288 --> 09:15.811
super sad heart song.

09:15.892 --> 09:18.334
Like his soul was breaking.

09:18.414 --> 09:19.976
But he swears he's fine,

09:20.056 --> 09:21.457
and actually,

09:21.537 --> 09:23.259
I mean, he did seem fine.

09:23.339 --> 09:25.381
- Well, as Detective
Olivia Benson would say,

09:25.461 --> 09:27.063
"He's lying!"

09:27.143 --> 09:29.145
That wasn't worth it.
I spilled my coffee everywhere

09:29.225 --> 09:30.386
and on me.

09:30.466 --> 09:32.348
- What if he's not lying,
though?

09:32.428 --> 09:34.230
Is the universe messing
with me?

09:34.310 --> 09:36.712
I mean, the songs have never
been wrong before.

09:36.792 --> 09:39.956
- Honestly,
as Olivia would also say,

09:40.036 --> 09:42.118
the easiest solution
is always the right one.

09:42.198 --> 09:44.720
Sounds like to me

09:44.800 --> 09:47.443
that you need
to interrogate the suspect

09:47.523 --> 09:51.167
and get him to sing again.

09:51.247 --> 09:53.930
Oh, I need my own cop show.

09:54.690 --> 09:57.293
- So you're really
not depressed

09:57.373 --> 09:59.495
at all, like, at all, at all?

09:59.575 --> 10:00.856
- No, I'm happy.

10:00.937 --> 10:02.378
Now can you pass me a sugar,
please?

10:02.458 --> 10:06.062
- Sounds like somebody's trying
to change the subject.

10:06.142 --> 10:07.503
Is that because
something really bad

10:07.583 --> 10:08.864
happened with Rose?

10:08.945 --> 10:11.027
- Zoey, I don't know
what to tell you, okay?

10:11.107 --> 10:12.828
We had a really awesome night.

10:12.908 --> 10:14.030
I won her an inflatable bear,

10:14.110 --> 10:15.711
we got our faces painted,

10:15.791 --> 10:18.074
then we got stuck
on the Ferris wheel

10:18.154 --> 10:19.715
and I learned a really dark
secret about her.

10:19.795 --> 10:21.077
- What?

10:21.157 --> 10:23.239
- She's a giant fan of
Blake Shelton.

10:23.319 --> 10:24.800
I know.
I'm still processing it.

10:24.880 --> 10:26.682
- You know,
it's funny you mention that,

10:26.762 --> 10:29.165
because I'm actually
thinking of telling Simon

10:29.245 --> 10:31.167
my biggest secret.

10:31.247 --> 10:32.768
- You're gonna tell him
about the powers?

10:32.848 --> 10:33.729
- Yes.

10:33.809 --> 10:35.091
No?

10:35.171 --> 10:36.212
Maybe.

10:36.292 --> 10:37.333
What do you think?

10:37.413 --> 10:39.375
- I'm not sure.

10:39.455 --> 10:42.418
I mean, I know honesty
is really important,

10:42.498 --> 10:44.380
but knowing
you could hear my songs

10:44.460 --> 10:46.502
really made
everything much more

10:46.582 --> 10:48.985
complicated between us.

10:49.065 --> 10:50.466
Things never felt equal,

10:50.546 --> 10:51.627
you know?

10:51.707 --> 10:53.709
- Hm.

10:55.071 --> 10:56.832
[percussive music]

10:56.912 --> 10:57.994
[elevator dings]

10:58.074 --> 10:59.555
♪ ♪

10:59.635 --> 11:01.477
- Hey, how's it going?

11:01.557 --> 11:03.079
- Confusing.

11:03.159 --> 11:04.800
Emily just sent me a video

11:04.880 --> 11:06.402
of a panda
licking a popsicle.

11:06.482 --> 11:08.724
- I've seen it.
It's cute.

11:08.804 --> 11:10.526
Oh, what about that psychic?

11:10.606 --> 11:12.928
- Oh, uh, yeah.
You were right.

11:13.009 --> 11:15.171
- I told you those people
can be shady.

11:15.251 --> 11:18.614
Oh, it turns out my very
exclusive woodworking club

11:18.694 --> 11:21.137
is open to having
a guest this week.

11:21.217 --> 11:22.578
Are you interested?

11:22.658 --> 11:24.100
- Are you kidding?

11:24.180 --> 11:26.102
All I've ever wanted is to see
the inner workings

11:26.182 --> 11:27.543
of an elite woodworking club.

11:27.623 --> 11:29.665
- Oh, my gosh.
You're not gonna regret it.

11:29.745 --> 11:31.547
- Hey, how is the

11:31.627 --> 11:35.151
"Great Microphone versus
Megaphone Debate" going?

11:35.231 --> 11:38.314
- I will tell you
after I grab this.

11:38.394 --> 11:40.476
- Uh, I would like to file a
corporate espionage complaint

11:40.556 --> 11:41.837
against the Microphone team.

11:41.917 --> 11:43.119
- What is that?

11:43.199 --> 11:44.360
- Whatever it is,
it's big and dumb.

11:44.440 --> 11:45.441
- I think the words
you're looking for

11:45.521 --> 11:46.602
are "awesome
and game changing."

11:46.682 --> 11:48.404
We had the guys
from R&amp;D make it.

11:48.484 --> 11:50.646
- Oh, well we also asked R&amp;D
to build us a mock-up,

11:50.726 --> 11:53.809
and it's so small and chic,

11:53.889 --> 11:57.093
you didn't even notice
we all had one right now.

11:57.173 --> 11:58.974
- That's the Microphone?

11:59.055 --> 12:02.818
That looks like the tiny,
sad baby of two hot Megaphones

12:02.898 --> 12:04.660
that got together,
didn't use protection,

12:04.740 --> 12:05.821
and now their lives
are ruined by all of you.

12:05.901 --> 12:07.303
- Yeah?
- Yeah!

12:07.383 --> 12:08.784
- You're wrong.
- Oh, I'm wrong?

12:08.864 --> 12:10.706
You're delusional.
- Okay, well--

12:10.786 --> 12:14.590
[upbeat music]

12:14.670 --> 12:18.194
- ♪ One is
the loneliest number ♪

12:18.274 --> 12:21.117
♪ That you'll ever do ♪

12:22.598 --> 12:26.162
♪ Two can be as bad as one ♪

12:26.242 --> 12:31.287
♪ It's the loneliest number
since the number one ♪

12:38.614 --> 12:41.817
♪ 'Cause one
is the loneliest number ♪

12:41.897 --> 12:46.262
♪ That you'll ever do ♪

12:46.342 --> 12:49.945
♪ One is the loneliest number ♪

12:50.025 --> 12:52.588
♪ Worse than two ♪

12:52.668 --> 12:55.111
- This does not
seem like a song

12:55.191 --> 12:56.912
you should
all be singing right now.

12:56.992 --> 12:59.715
- ♪ It's just
no good anymore ♪

12:59.795 --> 13:03.639
♪ Since you went away ♪

13:03.719 --> 13:06.041
♪ Now I spend my time ♪

13:06.122 --> 13:10.005
♪ Just making rhymes
of yesterday ♪

13:12.448 --> 13:16.051
♪ One is the loneliest number ♪

13:16.132 --> 13:20.015
♪ One is the loneliest number ♪

13:20.095 --> 13:23.659
♪ One is the loneliest number ♪

13:23.739 --> 13:27.183
♪ That you'll ever do ♪

13:30.146 --> 13:32.067
- Well, I think
the Microphone is better.

13:32.148 --> 13:34.390
- I-I-I think that you

13:34.470 --> 13:36.552
should all just

13:36.632 --> 13:38.714
keep debating it.

13:41.957 --> 13:45.401
[percussive music]

13:45.481 --> 13:48.404
[cellphone buzzing and chiming]

13:48.484 --> 13:50.366
♪ ♪

13:50.446 --> 13:52.208
- Wait up.
- Nuh-uh.

13:52.288 --> 13:54.410
- Sorry.

13:56.372 --> 13:58.414
- Many texts

13:58.494 --> 14:00.936
from Brad.

14:01.016 --> 14:02.498
- Your ex? Who cares?
I don't care.

14:02.578 --> 14:04.340
- He can't find our son's
stuffed animal.

14:04.420 --> 14:07.183
- Oh, a stuffed animal.
A tragedy.

14:07.263 --> 14:08.824
- I'm gonna have to go back
home and look for it.

14:08.904 --> 14:10.386
- Brad can't find it?

14:10.466 --> 14:12.348
- I think it's at my place.

14:12.428 --> 14:13.909
I'm really sorry,

14:13.989 --> 14:16.552
but my son
has to have it to sleep.

14:16.632 --> 14:18.634
It's a whole thing.

14:19.995 --> 14:21.997
Hopefully, it'll be quick.

14:22.518 --> 14:24.520
I'll text you.

14:28.924 --> 14:30.406
- There you are.

14:30.486 --> 14:32.408
I was sneaking in
to return Dad's watch

14:32.488 --> 14:34.610
so I didn't interrupt
your dinner party.

14:34.690 --> 14:35.811
- It's already over.

14:35.891 --> 14:37.373
- Oh, wow,
so it was really fun?

14:37.453 --> 14:38.894
- Fun if you like hearing about

14:38.974 --> 14:41.056
Clifford and Pamela's
Alaskan cruise adventure

14:41.136 --> 14:43.819
or Leslie and Jeff's doubles
tennis tournament.

14:43.899 --> 14:45.741
- Who won?

14:45.821 --> 14:47.463
- I don't know.

14:47.543 --> 14:50.226
I blacked out after Leslie made
me feel her thigh muscles.

14:50.306 --> 14:51.347
- Yikes.

14:51.427 --> 14:53.589
That must have been rough.

14:53.669 --> 14:55.511
- They just don't know

14:55.591 --> 14:57.473
how to be around me anymore,

14:57.553 --> 14:59.755
and clearly I don't know
how to be around them either.

14:59.835 --> 15:01.677
I think maybe I ought to just

15:01.757 --> 15:04.240
try to fly solo
for a little while,

15:04.320 --> 15:05.961
you know, take care
of numero uno,

15:06.041 --> 15:07.803
Maggie, party of--

15:07.883 --> 15:10.526
♪ Anything you can do,
I can do better ♪

15:10.606 --> 15:12.648
♪ I can do anything
better than you ♪

15:12.728 --> 15:14.250
♪ No you can't,
yes I can ♪

15:14.330 --> 15:15.651
♪ No you can't,
yes I can ♪

15:15.731 --> 15:16.852
♪ No you can't,
yes I can ♪

15:16.932 --> 15:18.934
♪ Yes I can ♪

15:21.497 --> 15:23.419
- Wait, you're singing two
different people's parts.

15:23.499 --> 15:26.181
- ♪ Sooner or later
I'm greater than you ♪

15:26.262 --> 15:27.863
♪ No you're not,
yes I am ♪

15:27.943 --> 15:29.184
♪ No you're not,
yes I am ♪

15:29.265 --> 15:31.186
♪ No you're not,
yes I am, yes I am ♪

15:31.267 --> 15:32.748
- This should
be the programmers' song,

15:32.828 --> 15:34.830
and their song was yours.

15:36.231 --> 15:37.593
- ♪ I can jump a hurdle ♪

15:37.673 --> 15:38.834
♪ I can wear a girdle ♪

15:38.914 --> 15:40.195
♪ I can knit a sweater ♪

15:40.276 --> 15:41.637
♪ I can fill it better ♪

15:41.717 --> 15:44.119
♪ I can do most anything ♪

15:44.199 --> 15:45.521
♪ Can you bake a pie? ♪

15:45.601 --> 15:47.803
♪ No,
neither can I ♪

15:47.883 --> 15:49.685
[line trilling]

15:49.765 --> 15:52.568
♪ Anything you can wear,
I can wear better ♪

15:52.648 --> 15:54.330
♪ In what you wear
I'd look better than you ♪

15:54.410 --> 15:55.651
- Hello?

15:55.731 --> 15:57.333
- Mo, I think I know
what's going on.

15:57.413 --> 15:58.894
The songs aren't wrong.

15:58.974 --> 16:00.976
They're just switched.

16:03.699 --> 16:06.942
- And then just as we were
heading to the bedroom,

16:07.022 --> 16:08.824
he gets a text message
saying that he had

16:08.904 --> 16:11.667
a stuffed animal emergency,
and then he left.

16:11.747 --> 16:12.868
- Can I have this?

16:12.948 --> 16:15.471
- Huh? Yeah.
- Mm.

16:15.551 --> 16:17.112
- What do you mean
songs are switching?

16:17.192 --> 16:20.115
- What I mean is that
the programmers at work

16:20.195 --> 16:21.917
sang my mom's heart song

16:21.997 --> 16:24.600
and my mom
sang their heart song.

16:24.680 --> 16:27.803
- But why, Zoey?
Why?

16:27.883 --> 16:30.526
- That's exactly
what we have to find out, okay?

16:30.606 --> 16:32.247
- I mean,

16:32.328 --> 16:34.089
the only thing I know for real

16:34.169 --> 16:35.611
is that Max
is telling the truth.

16:35.691 --> 16:37.973
That super sad song he sang

16:38.053 --> 16:39.174
belongs to someone else.

16:39.254 --> 16:41.617
- But who, Zoey?

16:41.697 --> 16:43.379
Who?

16:43.459 --> 16:45.901
- I don't know, but clearly
someone out there needs me,

16:45.981 --> 16:47.623
and I don't know what I did t--
I know what I did.

16:47.703 --> 16:50.025
I went with you
to that psychic.

16:50.105 --> 16:52.868
- Ah, don't you dare
blame this on Nova.

16:52.948 --> 16:55.230
[knocking on door]

16:55.310 --> 16:56.952
I don't know
what you are doing

16:57.032 --> 16:58.994
and going through,
but stop it.

16:59.074 --> 17:01.076
You got me all jumpy.

17:04.720 --> 17:07.443
- Hey. I just wanted
to stop by and apologize.

17:07.523 --> 17:09.044
Well hey, Zoey.

17:09.124 --> 17:10.526
- Hey.

17:10.606 --> 17:12.568
- I'm sorry, Perry,
I can't talk right now.

17:12.648 --> 17:15.371
I'm hosting a friend
who has an actual emergency.

17:15.451 --> 17:17.493
- Okay.

17:17.573 --> 17:19.254
- I hear you, I just...

17:19.334 --> 17:22.097
[country rock music]

17:22.177 --> 17:24.700
♪ ♪

17:24.780 --> 17:27.262
- ♪ He was sittin' at the bar ♪

17:27.342 --> 17:29.505
♪ Sippin' on a regular Coke ♪

17:29.585 --> 17:31.707
- Oh, no.

17:31.787 --> 17:33.429
Not you, too.

17:33.509 --> 17:35.671
- ♪ We were
drinkin' and smokin' ♪

17:35.751 --> 17:38.634
♪ And makin' him
the butt of our jokes ♪

17:41.517 --> 17:46.241
♪ We all said "Man, what
happened to you ♪

17:46.321 --> 17:50.045
♪ Why can't you
just have a few?" ♪

17:50.125 --> 17:52.728
♪ He said,
"I would if I could ♪

17:52.808 --> 17:55.771
♪ But it's probably best
that I don't" ♪

17:57.933 --> 18:00.295
♪ 'Cause the more I drink ♪

18:00.375 --> 18:03.018
♪ The more I drink ♪

18:03.098 --> 18:05.260
♪ Well, I'm the world's
greatest lover ♪

18:05.340 --> 18:07.262
♪ And a dancing machine ♪

18:07.342 --> 18:09.425
♪ I get loud ♪

18:09.505 --> 18:11.266
♪ I get proud ♪

18:11.346 --> 18:13.429
♪ And it gets worse ♪

18:15.270 --> 18:17.473
♪ Well if I have one ♪

18:17.553 --> 18:20.355
♪ I'll have 13 ♪

18:20.436 --> 18:23.719
♪ Nah, there ain't
no in between ♪

18:23.799 --> 18:27.963
♪ 'Cause the more I drink ♪

18:28.043 --> 18:31.607
♪ The more I drink ♪

18:34.089 --> 18:35.971
- Sometimes I have to
do these things,

18:36.051 --> 18:37.773
and that's all
I have to say about it.

18:37.853 --> 18:39.014
- Perry.

18:39.094 --> 18:41.256
- I'll text you.

18:43.979 --> 18:45.581
- Can you believe
this man showing up

18:45.661 --> 18:46.742
to my apartment unannounced.

18:46.822 --> 18:48.343
This is why I have a strict

18:48.423 --> 18:49.985
"not before noon" policy.

18:50.065 --> 18:51.707
Now, where are we?
- I'll tell you where we are.

18:51.787 --> 18:53.509
Making things more complicated.

18:53.589 --> 18:58.193
You just sang country.

18:58.273 --> 18:59.835
- Oh, now I know
something's wrong

18:59.915 --> 19:01.637
because I never sing country.

19:01.717 --> 19:03.158
- What did you do to me?

19:03.238 --> 19:05.160
- Do to you?
- Yeah.

19:05.240 --> 19:07.362
- You mean other
than use my gift

19:07.442 --> 19:10.285
to help you,
another human being?

19:10.365 --> 19:12.488
You do not understand
what it is like

19:12.568 --> 19:13.769
to have powers, Zoey.

19:13.849 --> 19:15.170
- Mo, how do I explain this?

19:15.250 --> 19:16.411
- You're not the only
redhead with powers.

19:16.492 --> 19:18.133
- Just like that, I guess.

19:18.213 --> 19:19.735
- How special we talking?

19:19.815 --> 19:20.936
- I don't want to brag,

19:21.016 --> 19:23.218
but I can hear people singing

19:23.298 --> 19:25.380
their innermost feelings
through popular music.

19:25.460 --> 19:27.062
- Wow.
That is interesting.

19:27.142 --> 19:28.303
I have never
heard that before,

19:28.383 --> 19:29.985
though I did once
know a boy who had

19:30.065 --> 19:31.587
an actual eye for talent.

19:31.667 --> 19:33.348
- Yeah-yeah-yeah, okay,
so I'm just wondering

19:33.428 --> 19:35.030
what you did to me,
because people's songs

19:35.110 --> 19:36.271
are getting switched
with other people.

19:36.351 --> 19:38.033
- How would I do that?

19:38.113 --> 19:40.355
You know what though, let's not
guess what the spirits want.

19:40.435 --> 19:42.437
Let's ask them, come on.

19:45.961 --> 19:48.363
Oh.

19:48.443 --> 19:50.606
The spirits are speaking.

19:50.686 --> 19:51.927
Oh, they're speaking a lot.

19:52.007 --> 19:54.890
[stammering]
M? M-M.

19:54.970 --> 19:57.773
M. Do you have
an M name in your life?

19:57.853 --> 19:59.895
- M, as in Mitch?

20:00.896 --> 20:03.619
Because that's my dad's name,
which you know.

20:03.699 --> 20:04.820
- Right, oh, yeah.

20:04.900 --> 20:07.743
[humming]

20:10.465 --> 20:12.147
- You know what?
It's okay. Fine.

20:12.227 --> 20:14.550
Thank you for your time
and the beverages.

20:14.630 --> 20:16.712
- And for...

20:16.792 --> 20:18.193
blessing you

20:18.273 --> 20:20.115
with my abilities

20:20.195 --> 20:22.718
for the second time.

20:22.798 --> 20:24.800
You're welcome.

20:26.762 --> 20:28.443
- You made her big mad.

20:28.523 --> 20:30.606
- But seriously?
Starts with M?

20:30.686 --> 20:32.648
How is this helping at all
with the song switching?

20:32.728 --> 20:33.969
- You know what all this
song switching reminds me of?

20:34.049 --> 20:35.651
"Freaky Friday."

20:35.731 --> 20:37.412
- I love that movie.
I used to watch it with--

20:37.492 --> 20:39.895
Oh, I just got the chills.

20:41.937 --> 20:44.499
"Freaky Friday"
was my favorite movie

20:44.580 --> 20:46.662
to watch with my dad.

20:46.742 --> 20:49.384
- And Nova mentioned movies
in our first session.

20:49.464 --> 20:51.106
Oh, I got the chills too.

20:51.186 --> 20:53.148
- In the movie they had to
figure out something

20:53.228 --> 20:55.310
to undo the switch, right?

20:55.390 --> 20:57.833
Maybe I have to figure out
something to undo mine.

20:57.913 --> 20:59.354
- Who sang what song?
- And then help those people.

20:59.434 --> 21:02.157
- Mm-hmm.
- That makes sense, okay?

21:02.237 --> 21:04.199
Now all I have to do is figure
out who sang the mystery song.

21:04.279 --> 21:06.001
Oh, the sad one
and the country one.

21:06.081 --> 21:07.683
And then the switch is over.

21:07.763 --> 21:09.204
- And how are you
gonna do that?

21:09.284 --> 21:10.165
- Harass everyone I know
until they burst

21:10.245 --> 21:11.126
into a musical number.

21:11.206 --> 21:13.288
- Attagirl.

21:15.050 --> 21:16.091
- Knock, knock.

21:16.171 --> 21:17.252
Are you busy?

21:17.332 --> 21:19.094
- For you?
No.

21:19.174 --> 21:21.777
For everyone else?
Yes.

21:21.857 --> 21:23.859
Walk with me.

21:23.939 --> 21:25.380
Is something going on, Zoey?

21:25.460 --> 21:27.142
- I'm just checking on
how you're doing and feeling,

21:27.222 --> 21:30.866
'cause if you're sad
and you're craving a drink

21:30.946 --> 21:32.828
but you're worried it could
lead to more drinking,

21:32.908 --> 21:34.630
you could always...

21:34.710 --> 21:36.471
think it?

21:36.551 --> 21:37.833
- What?
Worried about drinking coffee?

21:37.913 --> 21:40.235
- No, I meant booze.

21:40.315 --> 21:41.797
Are you
self-medicating with booze?

21:41.877 --> 21:42.798
- Is there something
going on, Zoey?

21:42.878 --> 21:44.519
- I don't know, is there?

21:44.599 --> 21:45.921
You could tell me.

21:46.001 --> 21:47.122
What are you thinking?

21:47.202 --> 21:49.004
What are you feeling?

21:49.084 --> 21:50.445
You don't even have
to tell me with your mouth.

21:50.525 --> 21:51.687
You could tell me
with your heart

21:51.767 --> 21:54.489
or your brain.

21:54.569 --> 21:56.171
No pressure.

21:56.251 --> 21:59.134
[dance club music]

21:59.214 --> 22:05.981
♪ ♪

22:06.061 --> 22:09.745
- ♪ Dog goes woof,
cat goes meow ♪

22:09.825 --> 22:13.348
♪ Bird goes tweet and
the mouse goes squeak ♪

22:13.428 --> 22:17.312
♪ Cow goes moo,
frog goes croak ♪

22:17.392 --> 22:19.835
♪ And the elephant goes toot ♪

22:19.915 --> 22:21.316
- Oh. Wow.

22:21.396 --> 22:24.840
- ♪ Ducks say quack,
and fish go blub ♪

22:24.920 --> 22:28.523
♪ And the seal goes ow ow ow ♪

22:28.603 --> 22:31.406
♪ But there's one sound
that no one knows ♪

22:31.486 --> 22:34.129
- I actually, I know.

22:34.209 --> 22:36.892
- ♪ What does the fox say? ♪

22:36.972 --> 22:38.974
♪ Ring-ding-ding-ding
dingeringeding ♪

22:39.054 --> 22:40.936
♪ Gering-ding-ding-ding
dingeringeding ♪

22:41.016 --> 22:43.218
♪ Gering-ding-ding-ding
dingeringeding ♪

22:43.298 --> 22:44.459
♪ What the fox say? ♪

22:44.539 --> 22:46.421
♪ Wa-pa-pa-pa-pa-pa-pow ♪

22:46.501 --> 22:50.065
♪ Wa-pa-pa-pa-pa-pa-pow,
wa-pa-pa-pa-pa-pa-pow ♪

22:50.145 --> 22:52.948
♪ What the fox say?

22:55.510 --> 22:57.032
There's nothing going on in my
brain right now, but--

22:57.112 --> 22:58.593
Wait, you are still coming to
my woodworking class

22:58.673 --> 22:59.875
tonight right?

22:59.955 --> 23:02.918
- You bet I'll be there,
you sly fox.

23:08.924 --> 23:09.805
.

23:09.885 --> 23:11.046
- This is getting
out of control.

23:11.126 --> 23:12.527
I'm starting to lose track of

23:12.607 --> 23:14.609
who's singing what,

23:14.689 --> 23:17.612
who's feeling what,

23:17.692 --> 23:20.896
and there is clearly still that

23:20.976 --> 23:22.417
poor soul

23:22.497 --> 23:24.419
in real need out there.

23:24.499 --> 23:26.421
- Hm, lucky for you,

23:26.501 --> 23:27.783
you've come
to the perfect person

23:27.863 --> 23:28.744
to help you crack this.

23:28.824 --> 23:30.225
Come on, kid.

23:30.305 --> 23:31.867
- Wow.

23:31.947 --> 23:33.789
This is impressive.
- Ain't she a beaut?

23:33.869 --> 23:35.470
Like to use this
when I want to solve

23:35.550 --> 23:37.152
crime mystery murders.

23:37.232 --> 23:38.593
On this side, you have
all the M's in your life.

23:38.673 --> 23:41.236
Maggie, Mitch, Me, Max,

23:41.316 --> 23:43.598
little baby Miles, Mackenzie.

23:43.678 --> 23:45.921
On this side, everyone
that you've encountered lately.

23:46.001 --> 23:47.843
Post-it notes, songs.

23:47.923 --> 23:49.444
- Hot delivery guy?

23:49.524 --> 23:51.366
- It could be anyone, Zoey.

23:51.446 --> 23:52.768
Even hot people.

23:52.848 --> 23:54.689
- Okay, add one to Simon,

23:54.770 --> 23:57.252
because he sang
"What Does the Fox Say?"

23:57.332 --> 23:59.054
at work.

23:59.134 --> 24:00.575
I mean, who would sing that?

24:00.655 --> 24:02.097
Why would they sing that?
It's insane.

24:02.177 --> 24:03.338
- Let's start with
what we know.

24:03.418 --> 24:04.820
- Okay, my mom

24:04.900 --> 24:05.901
switched songs
with the programmers,

24:05.981 --> 24:07.022
so we can match those.

24:07.102 --> 24:09.384
- Hey-hey, see? Progress.

24:09.464 --> 24:10.826
- Is there anyone else
we can match?

24:10.906 --> 24:12.587
- Simon

24:12.667 --> 24:14.029
and Max, [whistles] switched.

24:14.109 --> 24:15.430
- That would mean that

24:15.510 --> 24:17.552
Max's actual heart song is
"What Does the Fox Say?"

24:17.632 --> 24:20.435
and that would mean
he is a crazy person.

24:20.515 --> 24:21.877
[cell phone ding]

24:21.957 --> 24:24.559
And another text from Emily.

24:25.801 --> 24:27.562
She's stuck in a meeting

24:27.642 --> 24:29.044
and wants to
get a drink after work?

24:29.124 --> 24:30.685
She's never
asked me that ever.

24:30.765 --> 24:33.408
- Could Emily
be the country drinking song?

24:33.488 --> 24:34.649
She wants to have
a drink with you.

24:34.729 --> 24:35.811
A drink.

24:35.891 --> 24:37.973
- Yes!

24:38.053 --> 24:39.935
Wait, no, no.

24:40.015 --> 24:42.257
She's still
breastfeeding Miles, and--

24:42.337 --> 24:43.698
No, that song
is about someone with

24:43.778 --> 24:44.699
an actual drinking problem.

24:44.779 --> 24:46.741
There's no way that's her.

24:46.822 --> 24:48.503
Pump and dump.
I'mma keep her on the list

24:48.583 --> 24:49.744
just in case.

24:49.825 --> 24:51.586
- Oh, wait.
Oh, my God.

24:51.666 --> 24:54.429
Max told me that Rose
likes country music.

24:54.509 --> 24:55.911
Could Rose
be the drinking song?

24:55.991 --> 24:57.672
- You want me to follow her?

24:57.752 --> 24:59.754
I have a Burberry trench coat
that I have been dying to wear.

24:59.835 --> 25:01.316
- No need.
You want to know why?

25:01.396 --> 25:02.878
'Cause I know

25:02.958 --> 25:05.320
exactly where she's
gonna be tonight.

25:08.803 --> 25:10.525
We walk in,

25:10.605 --> 25:12.007
talk to Rose,
hopefully get her to sing,

25:12.087 --> 25:13.448
get out,
and then I go meet Simon

25:13.528 --> 25:15.490
for a good ol' fashion
woodworking date.

25:15.570 --> 25:18.573
- I'm starting to realize
you don't know what dates are.

25:18.653 --> 25:21.176
- Hey, guys.
Thank you so much for coming.

25:21.256 --> 25:22.978
There's a lot of
cool reconstituted

25:23.058 --> 25:25.580
old tech here,
but you might want to avoid

25:25.660 --> 25:28.263
the Furby autopsy room
in the back.

25:28.343 --> 25:29.704
I didn't need to see that.

25:29.784 --> 25:31.786
[glass clicking]

25:32.627 --> 25:35.871
- Everybody,
please pay attention to me.

25:35.951 --> 25:37.752
I'd like to thank

25:37.832 --> 25:39.875
the Martin and Reiner Gallery

25:39.955 --> 25:41.917
for their bravery

25:41.997 --> 25:44.519
in showcasing my vision.

25:44.599 --> 25:47.402
[cheers and applause]

25:47.482 --> 25:50.565
I'd also like to thank
the lovely Rosanna,

25:50.645 --> 25:52.928
who was an early champion
of my work.

25:53.008 --> 25:55.931
[cheers and applause]

25:56.011 --> 25:57.692
Take pics

25:57.772 --> 25:59.534
with your phones,

25:59.614 --> 26:01.216
which will one day
become the same

26:01.296 --> 26:03.378
obsolete garbage

26:03.458 --> 26:04.619
that you see
in front of you tonight.

26:04.699 --> 26:06.781
- [laughs]

26:08.703 --> 26:10.705
- It's not a joke.

26:12.227 --> 26:15.110
[light applause]

26:15.190 --> 26:16.191
- Hey.
- Hi.

26:16.271 --> 26:17.192
I'm so glad you both came.

26:17.272 --> 26:18.713
- Yeah, we did, we came.

26:18.793 --> 26:19.915
- Champagne?

26:19.995 --> 26:21.316
- Oh, yes, please.
- No, thank you.

26:21.396 --> 26:23.038
- Are you sure
you don't want one? It's free.

26:23.118 --> 26:24.759
- I'm fine, thank you.
- Did she stutter?

26:24.839 --> 26:26.321
- [chuckles]

26:26.401 --> 26:27.722
- Hey, Rose?
- We--

26:27.802 --> 26:29.124
- Oh, you know what?

26:29.204 --> 26:30.525
Would you excuse me
for just one second?

26:30.605 --> 26:31.686
- One.
